#Text=Or really much about anything .
#Text=Less so because of this technology that 's absorbed them , you know with their God damn ears closed and their eyes affixed .
#Text=and the God damn games they play .
#Text=It does n't get better as you go higher
#Text=It does n't ?
#Text=No , that was one of the things that stood out to me at Fordham Law .
#Text=It 's a top 25 law school in a very vibrant city with a lot of thinkers .
#Text=I told this anecdote to Floyd Abrams : I was in a Constitutional Law class right after Alito was nominated to be on the Supreme Court .
#Text=The professor asked 120 law students on the first day of class how many of them thought he should be confirmed .
#Text=About five students raised their hands .
#Text=" New York , " I thought .
#Text=Then he asked how many of them thought Alito should not be confirmed .
#Text=About ten students raised their hands .
#Text=Then he asked how many did not feel they had enough information to know .
#Text=about another five students raised their hands .
#Text=What is that ?
#Text=100 students in a Constitutional Law class at a top school ca n't proffer an opinion on a Supreme Court nominee ?
#Text=Is that apathy ... confusion ... fear ... ?
#Text=What is it ?
#Text=When I was in the military , there was no war .
#Text=1954 , 1955 ; Korea was over by then .
#Text=I had to camp with people from different parts of the United States .
#Text=Farmers , sons , rich people , poor people .

#Text=We were all together for at least six weeks of basic training , and then later on when you are assigned to a unit you really had a sense of the country if you did n't have the opportunity to travel .
#Text=Very few of us did ; I never traveled anywhere until I was in the army .
#Text=I went to college , from New Jersey to Alabama as a student , so I was at least in a different part of the United States than that where I was born .
#Text=Out of college I went into the army , Fort Knox , Kentucky , and I was with people from Texas , North Carolina and people from Boston .
#Text=Those who do n't have to serve , or choose not to , can say that it 's not their war .
#Text=But it 's an economic war ; it 's a sad commentary on who has to serve , because it is mercenary .
#Text=They are economic mercenaries .

#Text=They are economically deprived people , without opportunities , and they seek this opportunity and they never imagine how ill-chosen was their choice when they are missing a leg , or witnessing the horror .
#Text=It 's been close to five years , and still no protests ?
#Text=You do n't find the students at Columbia protesting ?
#Text=They can protest the President of Iran !
#Text=They 're good at that , but they are no good at protesting what is going on in to their generation that could n't afford to get into Columbia , or any place .
#Text=It 's so unfair , and so un-protested after so many years ...
#Text=it 's been close to five years !
